  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nIt seems that there's an issue with the latest version of `@ethereumjs/tx`. When running a Hardhat node, sending a call via :\r\n```bash\r\ncurl --data '{\"method\":\"eth_call\",\"params\":[{\"to\":\"0xa94f5374fce5edbc8e2a8697c15331677e6ebf0b\",\"data\":\"0xaa\"}, \"latest\"],\"id\":1,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST http://localhost:8545/\r\n```\r\n\r\nfails with `TypeError: Cannot read property 'gteHardfork' of undefined`.\r\n\r\nThe stack trace is:\r\n```\r\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'gteHardfork' of undefined\r\n    at new Transaction (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/@ethereumjs/tx/src/legacyTransaction.ts:112:17)\r\n    at new FakeSenderTransaction (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/transactions/FakeSenderTransaction.ts:92:5)\r\n    at HardhatNode._getFakeTransaction (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:1309:12)\r\n    at HardhatNode.runCall (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:417:27)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:97:5)\r\n    at EthModule._callAction (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:347:59)\r\n    at HardhatNetworkProvider._sendWithLogging (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:126:22)\r\n    at HardhatNetworkProvider.request (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:103:18)\r\n    at JsonRpcHandler._handleRequest (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/jsonrpc/handler.ts:188:20)\r\n    at JsonRpcHandler._handleSingleRequest (/home/nicolas/Workspace/moonce/godefi/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/jsonrpc/handler.ts:167:17)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe issue seems to be that `@ethereumjs/tx` relies on `this._validateTxV` [here](https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-monorepo/blob/103402bedb9c0adcb649761baaacd9ad7d38ec91/packages/tx/src/legacyTransaction.ts#L105) ; whereas it is overriden by Hardhat [here](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/81a1493e49db87d9741ffc69dc1f4e3d9deee47c/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/transactions/FakeSenderTransaction.ts#L157).\r\n\r\nI think one can just downgrade to the previous version of  `@ethereumjs/tx` for a temporary fix.",
